## Complete TDD Cycle Example

This example demonstrates the full 5-step cycle for creating a Tag entity:

```typescript
// ============================================
// STEP 0: REASON
// ============================================

// packages/tags/domain/entities/__tests__/tag.test.ts

import { describe, expect, test } from 'bun:test'
import { Tag } from '../tag'
import { TagName } from '../../value-objects/tag-name'
import { Id } from '../../value-objects/id'

describe('Tag Entity', () => {
  // TEST CASES LIST (Step 0: REASON)
  // Order: simple → complex
  // 
  // 1. ✓ Create tag with valid name (happy path - SIMPLEST)
  // 2. ✓ Get tag ID (basic accessor)
  // 3. ✓ Get tag name (basic accessor)
  // 4. ✓ Compare two tags for equality
  // 5. ✓ Convert tag to DTO
  // 6. ✓ Create tag from database data
  
  // Questions for Technical Lead:
  // - Should tags have unique names? YES (confirmed)
  // - Should tag names be case-insensitive? YES (confirmed)
  // - Maximum tag name length? 50 characters (confirmed)
  
  // Ready to proceed to Step 1: RED
  
  // ============================================
  // STEP 1: RED - First test (simplest)
  // ============================================
  
  test('should create tag with valid name', () => {
    // Arrange
    const name = TagName.create('Music')
    const id = Id.generate()
    
    // Act
    const tag = Tag.create({ id, name })
    
    // Assert
    expect(tag).toBeInstanceOf(Tag)
  })
  
  // Run test: ❌ Compilation error - "Tag.create does not exist"
  // GOOD - proves feature doesn't exist
  
  // Write MINIMUM to compile (in tag.ts):
  // export class Tag {
  //   static create(input: { id: Id; name: TagName }): Tag {
  //     throw new Error('Not implemented')
  //   }
  // }
  
  // Run test again: ❌ Test fails - "Not implemented"
  // PERFECT - RED phase complete
  
  // ============================================
  // STEP 2: GREEN - Simplest implementation
  // ============================================
  
  // In tag.ts:
  // export class Tag {
  //   private constructor(
  //     private readonly id: Id,
  //     private readonly name: TagName
  //   ) {}
  //   
  //   static create(input: { id: Id; name: TagName }): Tag {
  //     return new Tag(input.id, input.name) // TPP: nil→constant
  //   }
  // }
  
  // Run test: ✅ Test passes
  // GREEN phase complete
  
  // ============================================
  // STEP 3: REFACTOR
  // ============================================
  
  // Questions:
  // - Duplication? No
  // - Names clear? Yes (Tag, id, name)
  // - Need validation? Not yet, wait for more tests
  // - Extract anything? Not yet, only one test
  
  // Run tests: ✅ Still passing
  // REFACTOR complete (no changes needed)
  
  // ============================================
  // STEP 4: RE-EVALUATE
  // ============================================
  
  // TEST CASES LIST (Updated)
  // 1. ✅ Create tag with valid name (COMPLETE)
  // 2. ✓ Get tag ID (NEXT - still simplest)
  // 3. ✓ Get tag name
  // 4. ✓ Compare two tags for equality
  // 5. ✓ Convert tag to DTO
  // 6. ✓ Create tag from database data
  
  // Next: Write test for case #2
  // Return to Step 1: RED
  
  // ============================================
  // CYCLE 2: Second test
  // ============================================
  
  // STEP 1: RED
  test('should get tag ID', () => {
    const id = Id.generate()
    const name = TagName.create('Music')
    const tag = Tag.create({ id, name })
    
    expect(tag.getId()).toEqual(id)
  })
  
  // Run test: ❌ "Tag.getId does not exist"
  // Add method: getId(): Id { throw new Error('Not implemented') }
  // Run test: ❌ "Not implemented"
  // RED complete
  
  // STEP 2: GREEN
  // getId(): Id {
  //   return this.id // TPP: nil→constant
  // }
  // Run test: ✅ Passes
  // GREEN complete
  
  // STEP 3: REFACTOR
  // No changes needed, method is simple
  // REFACTOR complete
  
  // STEP 4: RE-EVALUATE
  // Move to case #3: Get tag name
  // Return to RED
  
  // ... Continue cycle for remaining test cases
})
```

## Integration with Existing Rules

This TDD cycle integrates with and enforces other project rules:

### Code Completeness (`.cursor/rules/code-completeness.mdc`)

- ✅ Tests ensure no TODOs remain (must implement to pass)
- ✅ Tests prevent empty implementations
- ✅ Tests verify all code paths work
- ✅ Tests catch incomplete error handling

### Biome Format and Validate (`.cursor/rules/biome-format-and-validate.mdc`)

**Workflow**:
1. Write test (RED)
2. Implement code (GREEN)
3. Refactor code (REFACTOR)
4. **Run Biome** on edited files
5. Fix any Biome errors
6. Re-run tests to ensure still green
7. Re-evaluate and continue

```bash
# After GREEN or REFACTOR phase
bunx --yes @biomejs/biome check --write <file-path>

# Verify tests still pass
bun test <test-file-path>
```

